import React from 'react';
import { Container, Typography, Link, List, ListItem, ListItemText } from '@mui/material';

function App() {
  return (
    <Container>
      <Typography variant="h1" gutterBottom>
        Copper
      </Typography>
      <Typography variant="body1" gutterBottom>
        Copper's objective is to make machine learning prototyping in Python as fast and intuitive as possible. It connects pandas and scikit-learn projects via the Dataset and Model Comparison classes.
      </Typography>
      <Typography variant="h2" gutterBottom>
        Examples
      </Typography>
      <List>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemText primary={<Link href="link-to-iris-classification-example">Iris Classification</Link>} />
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemText primary={<Link href="http://copper.readthedocs.com">Copper Documentation</Link>} />
        </ListItem>
      </List>
      <Typography variant="h2" gutterBottom>
        Requirements
      </Typography>
      <List>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemText primary="pandas" />
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemText primary="scikit-learn" />
        </ListItem>
      </List>
      <Typography variant="body1" gutterBottom>
        Note: The package is currently developed for Python 2.7 because scikit-learn does not support Python 3 yet. When scikit-learn supports Python 3, this project will drop support for Python 2 because all requirements will support Python 3.
      </Typography>
      <Typography variant="h2" gutterBottom>
        Installation
      </Typography>
      <Typography variant="body1" component="pre">
        pip install copper
      </Typography>
      <Typography variant="h2" gutterBottom>
        TODO
      </Typography>
      <List>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemText primary="Better tests for Model Comparison" />
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
          <ListItemText primary="Add missing metrics to Model Comparison" />
        </ListItem>
      </List>
      <Typography variant="h2" gutterBottom>
        License
      </Typography>
      <Typography variant="body1">
        This project is licensed under the GPL License - see the LICENSE.txt file for details.
      </Typography>
    </Container>
  );
}

export default App;
